# Design System Rules

## Components

- Use components from `src/components/` for all UI elements
- Toolbar, Canvas, PropertiesPanel, and ColorSwatches are the main UI components
- Import icons from `src/tools/icons/` (BrushIcon, EraserIcon, BlurIcon, FillIcon)
- Never create custom buttons, inputs, or panels - use the existing component patterns

## Tokens

- Use CSS variables for colors defined in `src/index.css`:
  - `var(--toolbar-bg)` - Dark background (#1e1e1e)
  - `var(--toolbar-border)` - Border color (#333)
  - `var(--button-hover)` - Hover state (#3a3a3a)
  - `var(--button-active)` - Active state (#4a4a4a)
  - `var(--accent-color)` - Primary accent (#6366f1)
- Use spacing scale: 8px (small), 12px (medium), 16px (large), 20px (section gap)
- Typography:
  - Labels: 11px, uppercase, letter-spacing 0.5px
  - Body text: 13px
  - Icon size: 22px

## Patterns

- Tool buttons: 44x44px, 8px border radius, 8px gap between buttons
- Action buttons: padding 10px 16px, 6px border radius, 8px gap between buttons
- Property sections: 20px vertical gap between sections, 8px gap within sections
- Panels: 16px padding, dark background with borders
- Color swatches: 28x28px, 4px border radius, 6px gap in grid
- Toolbar: 60px width, 12px vertical padding, 8px horizontal padding
- Properties panel: 240px width, 16px padding

## Colors

- Background: #2d2d2d (body), #1e1e1e (panels), #1a1a1a (canvas area)
- Text: white (primary), #ccc (secondary), #888 (tertiary), #666 (labels)
- Borders: #333 (primary), #444 (secondary)

## Transitions

- Use `transition: all 0.15s ease` for interactive elements
- Hover states should use `var(--button-hover)` background

## Files to reference

- `src/index.css` - All CSS variables and global styles
- `src/App.css` - Component-specific styles and patterns
- `src/components/Toolbar.jsx` - Tool button implementation
- `src/components/PropertiesPanel.jsx` - Panel and form patterns
- `src/components/ColorSwatches.jsx` - Color picker patterns
